<!-- UC-01 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-01 — Register Account</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Guest</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Email Service</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Allow a guest to register a new account to access platform features.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>The guest selects "Sign Up" from the landing page.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: The user is not currently signed in.<br>
    PRE2: The registration service is online and reachable.<br>
    PRE3: The guest provides a unique email address.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: A new user record is created in the database.<br>
    POST2: A verification OTP is generated and sent to the user.<br>
    POST3: User state is set to "PENDING_VERIFICATION".
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Guest opens the Sign Up page.<br>
    2. Guest fills in Email, Full Name, Password, and Role.<br>
    3. Guest completes the CAPTCHA.<br>
    4. Guest clicks "Register".<br>
    5. System validates data uniqueness.<br>
    6. System creates the account.<br>
    7. System sends OTP via email/SMS.<br>
    8. System redirects to Verification page.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Social Sign-up (Google): Guest uses Google OAuth to register.<br>
    AF2: Cancel Registration: Guest returns to landing page without saving.<br>
    AF3: Role Info: Guest clicks "Info" icon to see differences between Client/Broker roles.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Email Already Exists: System shows "Email in use" and suggests login.<br>
    E2: CAPTCHA Failure: System forces a refresh of the security challenge.<br>
    E3: Weak Password: System rejects submission until complexity met.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-01: Password must be 8+ chars with symbols/numbers.<br>
    BR-02: Users can only have one active profile per email address.<br>
    BR-03: Role cannot be changed once the account is verified without admin approval.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-02 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-02 — Verify Email</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Guest</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Verify account ownership via OTP code.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>User lands on verification screen after signup or login.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: An unverified account exists in the database.<br>
    PRE2: An active verification code has been sent.<br>
    PRE3: The user is currently on the verification page.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: User status is updated to "VERIFIED/ACTIVE".<br>
    POST2: Verification code is invalidated/deleted.<br>
    POST3: User is granted a persistent session token.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. User checks email for OTP.<br>
    2. User enters 6-digit code.<br>
    3. User clicks "Verify".<br>
    4. System matches code.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Resend Code: User clicks "Resend" after 60 seconds wait.<br>
    AF2: Incorrect Phone/Email: User goes back to edit registration info.<br>
    AF3: Manual Link: User clicks a link in the email instead of entering OTP.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Expired OTP: System prompts user to request a fresh code.<br>
    E2: Maximum Retries: System locks verification for 30 minutes after 5 fails.<br>
    E3: Invalid Input: System prevents non-numeric characters in OTP field.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-04: OTP expires exactly 5 minutes after generation.<br>
    BR-05: Verification is mandatory to use any marketplace features.<br>
    BR-06: Only 3 OTPs can be requested within a 15-minute window per IP.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-03 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-03 — Login</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>All Users</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Security Manager</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Authenticate user credentials to grant access.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>User accesses the Login page.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: User has a registered account.<br>
    PRE2: Account is not currently banned or suspended.<br>
    PRE3: User has internet connectivity.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Access and Refresh tokens are issued.<br>
    POST2: Login timestamp and IP are recorded in audit logs.<br>
    POST3: User is navigated to their specific dashboard.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. User enters Email/Password.<br>
    2. System verifies credentials.<br>
    3. System checks account status.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Remember Me: User checks box to extend session duration.<br>
    AF2: Social Login: User logs in via Google/Facebook login.<br>
    AF3: Switch Account: User logs out and returns to login screen.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Invalid Credentials: Error "Email or password incorrect".<br>
    E2: Unverified Account: System redirects to UC-02 (Verification).<br>
    E3: Brute Force: System triggers CAPTCHA after 3 failed attempts.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-07: Password hashing must use industry-standard algorithms (Bcrypt/Argon2).<br>
    BR-08: Session must expire after 24 hours of inactivity.<br>
    BR-09: Concurrent logins from different geographical regions trigger security alerts.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-04 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-04 — Forgot Password</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Guest</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, SMS/Email Gateway</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Reset password for users who lost access.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>User clicks "Forgot Password" on login screen.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: A registered account matching the email exists.<br>
    PRE2: User is not logged in.<br>
    PRE3: Account is in Active status.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Password is successfully updated.<br>
    POST2: All existing session tokens are invalidated.<br>
    POST3: Confirmation email of password change is sent.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. User enters Email.<br>
    2. System sends Reset OTP.<br>
    3. User verifies OTP.<br>
    4. User enters New Password.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Cancel Reset: User returns to login page midway.<br>
    AF2: Contact Support: User chooses to talk to admin if email is lost.<br>
    AF3: Recovery Link: User uses a unique URL from email instead of OTP.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Account Not Found: System shows generic success message for security.<br>
    E2: OTP Expired: Link/Code becomes invalid after 15 minutes.<br>
    E3: Same Password: System prevents using the current password as the new one.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>Medium</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-10: New passwords must not contain the user's name or known personal details.<br>
    BR-11: Account reset is locked if requested more than 5 times in 1 hour.<br>
    BR-12: Password reset tokens are one-time use and invalidated upon first use.
  </td></tr>
</table>

