  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-05 — View Public Landing Page</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Guest</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Display marketing and platform overview.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>User visits root URL.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: Web server is operational and reachable.<br>
    PRE2: Browser supports modern web standards.<br>
    PRE3: Static assets are cached or available on the network.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Marketing Landing Page is rendered correctly.<br>
    POST2: Anonymous guest tracking session is initialized.<br>
    POST3: Action buttons (Login/Sign Up) are accessible.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. User enters URL.<br>
    2. System loads landing components.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Language Switch: User changes site language via footer.<br>
    AF2: Dark Mode: User toggles UI theme preference.<br>
    AF3: Featured Projects: User scrolls to see public marketplace samples.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Asset Timeout: System shows placeholder colors if images fail.<br>
    E2: Script Error: Navigation remains functional via standard HTML links.<br>
    E3: Unsupported Browser: System shows a recommendation banner to update.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>Low</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-13: Landing page must meet accessibility (WCAG) contrast standards.<br>
    BR-14: Content must be indexable by major search engines (SEO optimized).<br>
    BR-15: Sample projects shown must be marked as 'Public' by their owners.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-06 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-06 — Manage Account</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Client, Broker, Freelancer</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Storage Bucket</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Update profile information and settings.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>User clicks "Profile Settings".</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: User has an active, authenticated session.<br>
    PRE2: User profile record exists and is fetched.<br>
    PRE3: User has appropriate permissions to modify their own data.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Updated profile data is persisted in the database.<br>
    POST2: Changes are reflected immediately in the UI headers.<br>
    POST3: System logs the specific fields changed for auditing.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. User edits Name/Avatar.<br>
    2. User clicks "Save".<br>
    3. System validates input.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Security Tab: User changes password or enables 2FA.<br>
    AF2: Deactivation: User requests to hide their profile from marketplace.<br>
    AF3: Preferences: User updates timezone or date format settings.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Storage Failure: Image upload fails, system reverts to old avatar.<br>
    E2: Validation Error: System highlights fields not meeting length requirements.<br>
    E3: Session Expired: System prompts for login before allowing the save.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>Medium</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-16: Display names cannot be changed more than twice in 30 days.<br>
    BR-17: Email address changes must be verified through the new address.<br>
    BR-18: Account roles (Client/Broker) cannot be swapped after initial verification.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-07 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-07 — Register KYC</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Client, Broker, Freelancer</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Admin Reviewer</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Submit identity verification documents for trust building.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>User selects "Verify Identity" from trust profile.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: Basic profile (UC-06) is completed.<br>
    PRE2: User is legally an adult (18+).<br>
    PRE3: User has high-resolution document scans ready.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: KYC status is updated to "PENDING_REVIEW".<br>
    POST2: Document files are moved to secure, encrypted storage.<br>
    POST3: Verification request is queued for administrative approval.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. User uploads ID documents.<br>
    2. User uploads verification selfie.<br>
    3. User clicks "Submit".
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Document Type: User switches between Citizen ID and Passport.<br>
    AF2: Retake Photo: User replaces doc images before final submission.<br>
    AF3: In-person Verify: User chooses to bring documents to a physical office (if available).
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Quality Filter: System rejects images with obscured text automatically.<br>
    E2: Data Mismatch: Name on ID differs from profile name significantly.<br>
    E3: Blacklisted: System flags document ID matching a banned user.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-19: KYC submissions must be reviewed by staff within 2 business days.<br>
    BR-20: All identity images must be uploaded in PNG or JPEG format.<br>
    BR-21: Identity verification is mandatory for project budgets exceeding $1,000.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-08 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-08 — Do Request Wizard</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Client</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Recommendation AI</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Guided multi-step questionnaire to define project requirements.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Client clicks "Create Request" button.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: Client is logged in and verified.<br>
    PRE2: System wizard metadata is loaded from backend.<br>
    PRE3: Client has not reached the concurrent request limit.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: A project draft is created and saved in the user's workspace.<br>
    POST2: Selected features and industry tags are categorized.<br>
    POST3: Client is moved to the final review/publish screen.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Select project type.<br>
    2. Select industry.<br>
    3. Set budget/timeline.<br>
    4. Select tech features.<br>
    5. Summarize project.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Use Draft: Client resumes a partially completed wizard session.<br>
    AF2: Import Specs: Client uploads a document to auto-fill wizard fields.<br>
    AF3: Consult AI: Client asks for suggestions for budget based on industry.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Step Validation: Client tries to skip mandatory industry selection.<br>
    E2: Range Overflow: Budget value exceeds platform maximum supported.<br>
    E3: Backend Timeout: System saves progress locally and retries sync.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-22: Drafts must be autosaved every time a user proceeds to a next step.<br>
    BR-23: A minimum of 3 specific technical features must be selected.<br>
    BR-24: Project titles must be unique within the client's own history.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-09 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-09 — Create Request</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Client</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Broker Matching Engine</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Finalize project definition and open it for bidding.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Client clicks "Post to Marketplace" button.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: Wizard steps (UC-08) are fully completed.<br>
    PRE2: Client account trust score is above the minimum threshold.<br>
    PRE3: Request title and description are validated for policy.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Request status is set to "PUBLIC_HIRING".<br>
    POST2: Marketplace search engine is updated with new request data.<br>
    POST3: Automated matching notifications are sent to relevant brokers.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Review summary.<br>
    2. Confirm publication.<br>
    3. System publishes.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Private Posting: Request is hidden from public list and is invite-only.<br>
    AF2: Priority Listing: Client pays to feature the request in marketplace.<br>
    AF3: Save as Private Draft: Client finishes definitions but does not publish.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Forbidden Content: System flags request for containing contact info.<br>
    E2: Credit Check: User's fee payment (if applicable) is declined.<br>
    E3: Duplicate Post: System prevents posting identical requests within 5 mins.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-25: Public requests are archived automatically after 30 days if no broker hired.<br>
    BR-26: Standard accounts are limited to 5 active marketplace listings.<br>
    BR-27: Descriptions must contain at least 200 characters to ensure clarity for brokers.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-10 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-10 — Invite Broker Directly</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Client</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>Broker, Notification Engine</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Request a specific broker to view and bid on a project.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Client clicks "Invite" on a broker's profile card.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: Client has at least one active request (Public or Private).<br>
    PRE2: Target Broker has a "Verified" status or high trust score.<br>
    PRE3: Broker's notification settings allow direct invites.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Invitation record is created in the recruitment subsystem.<br>
    POST2: Broker receives an instant notification with project link.<br>
    POST3: The project is added to the Broker's "Invited Jobs" board.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Browse Brokers.<br>
    2. Select Request.<br>
    3. Click "Send Invite".
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Bulk Invite: Client invites multiple top-rated brokers from a list.<br>
    AF2: Withdraw Invite: Client cancels the request before the broker responds.<br>
    AF3: Broker Suggestions: Client invites from a system-generated match list.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Already Invited: System prevents duplicate invites for the same project.<br>
    E2: Busy Status: Broker marked as "Not Available" for new invitations.<br>
    E3: Blocked User: Broker has previously blocked the client's account.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>Medium</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-28: Max invitations per project is capped to 15 to prevent spamming.<br>
    BR-29: Invitations expire automatically if not accepted within 48 hours.<br>
    BR-30: Direct invitation is required for any request marked as 'Private'.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-11 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-11 — Post Project To Marketplace</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Client</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Broker Community</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Move a project definition from draft status to active market listing.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Client clicks "Publish" on an existing project draft.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: Draft contains all required technical specifications.<br>
    PRE2: Project is not already live or cancelled.<br>
    PRE3: User is currently logged into a valid Client account.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Project status is updated to "PUBLIC_HIRING".<br>
    POST2: Visibility timestamp is set for expiration tracking.<br>
    POST3: Project is now searchable by all registered brokers.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Select draft.<br>
    2. Confirm fees.<br>
    3. Activate listing.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Featured Post: Client pays for enhanced visibility on the home page.<br>
    AF2: Limited Visibility: Listing visible only to "Top Rated" brokers.<br>
    AF3: Scheduled Live: Set a future date for the project to go public.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Missing Files: Draft requires mandatory spec files to be published.<br>
    E2: Fee Decline: Transaction for listing fee fails to process.<br>
    E3: Duplicate Title: System detects another active listing with same name.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-31: Only verified clients are allowed to post to the public marketplace.<br>
    BR-32: A project cannot be edit-locked until at least one proposal is received.<br>
    BR-33: Market listings are valid for 30 days before requiring renewal.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-12 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-12 — View List Request</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Client</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Review current status and details of all user-owned project requests.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Client accesses "My Requests" page from navigation.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: User is authenticated.<br>
    PRE2: User is the primary owner or manager of the requests.<br>
    PRE3: Dashboard service is operational.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: A comprehensive list of requests is displayed for the user.<br>
    POST2: Aggregated status counts (Total, Active, Draft) are shown.<br>
    POST3: User can trigger follow-up actions (Edit/Invite) from list.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Open dashboard.<br>
    2. Browse requests.<br>
    3. Apply filters.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Export Activity: Download project listing as an Excel document.<br>
    AF2: Search Keywords: Filter list by specific title or tech stack tags.<br>
    AF3: View Archive: Toggle to see closed/cancelled project history.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Empty State: User has no projects, system shows onboarding tips.<br>
    E2: Refresh Fail: System shows cached data with a "Sync Error" badge.<br>
    E3: Forbidden: Attempting to access list via shared link without login.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>Medium</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-34: Users must only see projects they created or have been shared with them.<br>
    BR-35: Completed projects are moved to the 'Archive' tab after 90 days.<br>
    BR-36: Real-time status updates are required for current active listings.
  </td></tr>
</table>

