  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Evaluate completed milestone work and authorize fund release.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Freelancer marks a milestone as "Delivered".</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: Milestone is in "Review" state.<br>
    PRE2: Proof of work assets (Git link, Files) are present.<br>
    PRE3: Total project funds are held in system escrow.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Funds for that milestone are released to the freelancer balance.<br>
    POST2: Milestone status is updated to "PAID".<br>
    POST3: Overall project progress % is recalculated and updated.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Inspect work.<br>
    2. Verify criteria.<br>
    3. Approve release.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Partial Rework: Approve part of the milestone, hold back 10% for fixes.<br>
    AF2: Dispute Submission: Formally reject the work due to scope mismatch.<br>
    AF3: Technical Audit: Ask the Broker to verify the quality before client clicks pay.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Invalid Proof: Sandbox detects empty or irrelevant files uploaded.<br>
    E2: Escrow Lock: System funds are temporarily frozen by admin for audit.<br>
    E3: Review Gap: Client fails to review, triggering auto-escalation.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-46: Milestone approval is irreversible and immediately releases funds from escrow.<br>
    BR-47: Clients have a 7-day window to review work before auto-approval (if not disputed).<br>
    BR-48: Proof of Work links must remain active for the entire duration of the project.
  </td></tr>
</table>

