    PRE2: Transaction amount is within system limits.<br>
    PRE3: User identity check (KYC) is successful for large amounts.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: External transaction is successfully polled from gateway.<br>
    POST2: Internal system credits/ledger are updated accurately.<br>
    POST3: Tax-compliant invoice is generated and emailed to user.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Select amount.<br>
    2. Confirm method.<br>
    3. Perform 3D Secure.<br>
    4. Receipt display.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Credit Balance: Use existing platform wallet credits for payment.<br>
    AF2: Installment Plan: Set up recurring payments for long-term projects.<br>
    AF3: Promo Application: Deduct platform service fees using a valid coupon.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Bank Decline: User's bank rejects transaction for "Insufficient Funds".<br>
    E2: Timeout: Gateway takes too long to respond, system queues the verify.<br>
    E3: Invalid Currency: Attempting to pay in a non-supported local currency.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-49: Platform charges a flat 5% fee on all deposits for escrow maintenance.<br>
    BR-50: Minimum transaction amount is $10.00 USD.<br>
    BR-51: All financial data must be encrypted and handled via PCI-DSS compliant providers.
  </td></tr>
</table>

