  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Allows clients to upgrade, downgrade, or cancel their platform subscription plans.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Client clicks "Plans & Billing" in account settings.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: Client is logged in and authenticated.<br>
    PRE2: A valid payment method is linked to the account.<br>
    PRE3: Client does not have any pending overdue invoices.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Subscription tier is updated in the user profile.<br>
    POST2: New usage limits (e.g., max concurrent projects) are applied immediately.<br>
    POST3: A confirmation receipt of the plan change is sent to the client's email.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Client views current plan details.<br>
    2. Client selects a new subscription tier.<br>
    3. Client confirms the pro-rated payment amount.<br>
    4. System processes the transaction via Stripe.<br>
    5. System updates the account features.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Switch to Annual: Client changes from monthly to yearly billing for a discount.<br>
    AF2: Manage Payment Method: Client updates the credit card used for the subscription.<br>
    AF3: View Invoices: Client downloads historical billing PDF documents.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Payment Failure: Stripe declines the card, plan remains on the current tier.<br>
    E2: Downgrade Blocked: Client has more active projects than allowed in the lower tier.<br>
    E3: Region Restriction: Selected plan is not available in the client's registered country.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>Medium</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-61: Plan downgrades take effect at the end of the current billing cycle.<br>
    BR-62: Upgrades are immediate and charged a pro-rated amount for the remaining days.<br>
    BR-63: Refunds for cancelled subscriptions are only granted within the first 24 hours of purchase.
  </td></tr>
</table>

