<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-22 — Manage Dispute (Client side)</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Client</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Admin Mediator</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Review and handle ongoing disputes raised against or by the client.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Client clicks on "Dispute Center" from the dashboard.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: At least one dispute record is linked to the client's ID.<br>
    PRE2: Client has an active session.<br>
    PRE3: Dispute status is either 'OPEN' or 'IN_MEDIATION'.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Dispute activity log is updated with user's viewing session.<br>
    POST2: Client's response or additional evidence is saved to the case file.<br>
    POST3: Case status moves to the next phase if a required action is completed.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Client filters list by 'Active' disputes.<br>
    2. Client selects a specific case to manage.<br>
    3. Client reviews the latest updates from the mediator.<br>
    4. Client performs a required action (e.g., accept split).
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Add Note: Client leaves a private clarification for the admin mediator.<br>
    AF2: Withdraw Case: Client decides to drop the dispute and release funds.<br>
    AF3: Message Defendant: Client uses the case-specific chat to resolve issues privately.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Decision Finalized: Client tries to edit a case that has already been resolved.<br>
    E2: Deadline Missed: Action buttons are disabled because the response window closed.<br>
    E3: Attachment Limit: Client tries to upload evidence exceeding 50MB in total.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-64: Clients must respond to mediator requests within 48 hours or risk default loss.<br>
    BR-65: Formal evidence once uploaded cannot be deleted from the audit trail.<br>
    BR-66: Disputes involving less than $50 are prioritized for automated split suggestions.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-23 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-23 — Create Dispute (Client side)</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Client</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Freelancer/Broker (Defendant)</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Formally report a problem with a project or milestone to trigger arbitration.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Client clicks "File a Dispute" on a project or milestone page.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: The project/milestone must be in an 'In-Progress' or 'Review' status.<br>
    PRE2: Client has attempted to contact the defendant via chat first.<br>
    PRE3: Funds for the specific milestone are currently held in escrow.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Milestone funds are locked and cannot be released until resolution.<br>
    POST2: Dispute ticket is generated and assigned a unique case ID.<br>
    POST3: Notification is sent to the defendant and the platform admin team.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Select project and milestone.<br>
    2. Choose dispute category (Quality, Deadline, Communication).<br>
    3. Describe the issue in detail.<br>
    4. Upload supporting screenshots/files.<br>
    5. Submit the case.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Request Partial Refund: Client proposes a specific % split to avoid full arbitration.<br>
    AF2: Draft Dispute: Save the form progress to submit later.<br>
    AF3: Link Chat Logs: System auto-attaches relevant project chat history to the case.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Milestone Paid: System prevents disputing work that has already been approved.<br>
    E2: Insufficient Data: Submission rejected for having a description shorter than 50 chars.<br>
    E3: Cool-down Period: Disputes cannot be filed within 24 hours of project start.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-67: Disputes automatically lock all associated project funds across all active milestones.<br>
    BR-68: Filing more than 2 invalid/frivolous disputes per month leads to account penalty.<br>
    BR-69: A filing fee (3% of escrow value) is held until the case outcome is decided.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-24 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-24 — View Dispute Information (Client side)</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Client</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Read the current status, timeline, and documents of a specific dispute.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Client clicks a dispute notification or list item.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: Dispute case exists and matches the user's role.<br>
    PRE2: User is logged in.<br>
    PRE3: Browser supports document preview features.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: All parties' arguments and evidence are displayed to the client.<br>
    POST2: Timeline of all previous mediator actions is visible.<br>
    POST3: Next steps and expected resolution dates are highlighted.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Open Dispute Summary.<br>
    2. View raiser's claim and defendant's response.<br>
    3. Check evidence attachments.<br>
    4. Read mediator's preliminary findings.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
