    2. System subscribes user to the project's WebSocket room.<br>
    3. User synchronizes message history.<br>
    4. User starts sending/receiving live messages.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Search History: Actor uses keyword search to find past discussions.<br>
    AF2: View Participants: Actor sees a list of currently online team members.<br>
    AF3: Mute Channel: Actor stays in the room but disables sound alerts.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Auth Failure: Session expired, user redirected to login.<br>
    E2: Server Offline: System displays "Socket.io connection failed, retrying...".<br>
    E3: Permission Revoked: User tries to enter a room for a cancelled project.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-91: All messages must be persisted in the database for at least 2 years.<br>
    BR-92: Chat rooms are automatically archived when a project is closed.<br>
    BR-93: Profanity filters are active on all public and project-level chat rooms.
  </td></tr>
</table>

