  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: Project is in 'IN_PROGRESS' status.<br>
    PRE2: Kanban board has been initialized for the project.<br>
    PRE3: User has 'Developer' or 'Manager' permissions.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Task position and column status are saved in the database.<br>
    POST2: Real-time update is sent to all other members viewing the board.<br>
    POST3: Audit log records the task movement (from-to columns).
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Actor drags a task card from 'Todo' to 'In Progress'.<br>
    2. Actor updates task description or assignee.<br>
    3. Actor attaches evidence or code references to the card.<br>
    4. Actor moves task to 'Done'.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Archive Completed: Move all 'Done' tasks to an archive list to clear the view.<br>
    AF2: Filter by Member: View only tasks assigned to a specific freelancer.<br>
    AF3: Priority Color-coding: Assign 'High/Medium/Low' labels to cards.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Forbidden Move: Moving a task to 'Done' without completing required sub-tasks.<br>
    E2: Concurrency Conflict: Two users try to move the same card simultaneously.<br>
    E3: Attachment Overload: Uploading more than 10 files to a single task card.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>Medium</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-94: Every task must be linked to at least one active milestone.<br>
    BR-95: Only Brokers can create new columns (swimlanes) on the board.<br>
    BR-96: Moving a task to 'Done' does NOT automatically approve the milestone.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-34 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-34 — Rate Freelancer/Client</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Broker</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Provide qualitative and quantitative feedback for team members or the client.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Broker completes a milestone or the entire project.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: The target actor (Freelancer or Client) was part of the same project.<br>
    PRE2: Project status is 'COMPLETED' or 'CANCELLED'.<br>
    PRE3: Broker has not already submitted a rating for this specific project.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Feedback score is added to the target's public profile.<br>
    POST2: Trust score of the target is recalculated based on weights.<br>
    POST3: Notification is sent to the target that they have received a review.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Select project and member.<br>
    2. Assign Star ratings for skills, communication, and punctuality.<br>
    3. Write a detailed review comment.<br>
    4. Submit review.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Private Feedback to Platform: Leave a note only visible to admins about the user.<br>
    AF2: Skip Review: Intentionally choose not to leave a review.<br>
    AF3: Update Review: Edit the text (but not stars) within a 24-hour window.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Timeout: Attempting to review after the 30-day review window has closed.<br>
    E2: Retaliation Detection: System flags a review that seems to be in response to a dispute loss.<br>
    E3: Character Limit: Comment is shorter than 20 characters.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>Medium</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-97: Ratings are binary-blind: neither side sees the other's score until both are done.<br>
    BR-98: Reviews including personal contact info are automatically flagged for removal.<br>
    BR-99: Brokers can only rate their direct subordinates (excluding other brokers).
  </td></tr>
</table>

