<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-36 — Edit Account Information</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Broker, Freelancer</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Email Service</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Update personal details, security settings, and professional preferences.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Actor clicks "Settings" in the profile menu.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: User is logged in and authenticated.<br>
    PRE2: Account is not in a 'Suspended' state.<br>
    PRE3: KYC status is 'VERIFIED' (if changing name/identity).
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Updated record is saved in the 'users' and 'profiles' tables.<br>
    POST2: Email verification is triggered if the email address changed.<br>
    POST3: Active sessions on other devices are invalidated for security.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Update contact number or location.<br>
    2. Change notification preferences (Email/Push).<br>
    3. Update professional bio.<br>
    4. Save changes.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Change Password: Actor updates credentials for security.<br>
    AF2: Deactivate Account: Actor requests temporary account hiding.<br>
    AF3: Link Social Media: Actor connects LinkedIn or GitHub for enhanced verification.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Duplicate Information: Attempting to use an email already registered to another user.<br>
    E2: Weak Password: New password fails the complexity check (BR-01).<br>
    E3: Modification Limit: Name change requested more than once in 180 days.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>Medium</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-100: Critical fields (Legal Name, Role) require admin approval to change after verification.<br>
    BR-101: All profile updates are logged for security auditing.<br>
    BR-102: Private profiles are hidden from the Marketplace search results.
  </td></tr>
</table>

