<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-38 — Manage Dispute (Provider side)</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Broker, Freelancer</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Admin Mediator</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Defend against or manage disputes raised by clients regarding work quality or delivery.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Actor receives a dispute notification or opens the Dispute Center.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: A dispute exists where the Actor is named as a defendant or plaintiff.<br>
    PRE2: Case status is active (Open, Mediation).<br>
    PRE3: Actor session is active.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Provider's defense statement is added to the case log.<br>
    POST2: New evidence attachments are timestamped and shared with the mediator.<br>
    POST3: Case timeline is updated with the latest action.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. View Details of the claim.<br>
    2. Submit a counter-argument/response.<br>
    3. Upload technical proof of delivery.<br>
    4. Acknowledge mediator's request for info.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Offer Partial Refund: Provider suggests a split of escrow funds to settle quickly.<br>
    AF2: Request Extension: Ask mediator for more time to gather logs/proof.<br>
    AF3: Private Note: Leave confidential technical details only for the mediator.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Deadline Expiry: Unable to respond because the 72-hour defense window closed.<br>
    E2: Decision Final: Attempting to edit response after mediator's verdict.<br>
    E3: File Blocked: Evidence contains a virus or malicious macro.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-106: Providers must respond to any dispute within 3 business days of notification.<br>
    BR-107: Failure to respond within the deadline results in automated loss of escrow funds.<br>
    BR-108: All disputed funds are frozen in escrow and cannot be released mid-process.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-39 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-39 — Create Dispute (Provider side)</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Broker, Freelancer</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Client (Defendant)</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Raise a formal claim against a client for non-payment or unreasonable scope changes.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Actor clicks "Dispute Payment" on a project page.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: Work was submitted >7 days ago with no client response.<br>
    PRE2: Funds for the milestone are currently held in escrow.<br>
    PRE3: Negotiation via chat has reached an impasse.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Dispute record created and assigned to the next available mediator.<br>
    POST2: Client's account is flagged for 'Active Dispute'.<br>
    POST3: Escrow release for current milestone is locked.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Select project and unpaid milestone.<br>
    2. Choose category (Non-payment, Scope Creep).<br>
    3. Provide evidence of work done vs requirements.<br>
    4. Submit complaint.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Draft Dispute: Save the claim as a draft before final submission.<br>
    AF2: Peer Witness: Link another project freelancer to verify the work completion.<br>
    AF3: Auto-dispute: System suggests filing a dispute if client is 14 days overdue.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Milestone Approved: Cannot dispute a milestone that has already been paid out.<br>
    E2: Insufficient Work: System rejects filing if no deliverables were uploaded.<br>
    E3: Policy Violation: Filing a dispute for a project value <$20.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-109: Filing a dispute prevents the Provider from starting new projects with that specific Client.<br>
    BR-110: A processing fee of 1% is deducted if the Provider loses the dispute.<br>
    BR-111: Validating evidence must strictly match the agreed technical requirements (DRS).
  </td></tr>
</table>

