    2. Propose a bid amount and estimated duration.<br>
    3. Attach relevant case studies or portfolio pieces.<br>
    4. Submit and wait for client shortlisting.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Withdraw Proposal: Remove application before the client has viewed it.<br>
    AF2: Edit Proposal: Update the bid or cover letter (if permitted by project settings).<br>
    AF3: Boost Application: Spend extra credits to put the proposal at the top of the client's list.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Credit Shortage: User tries to apply with 0 credits and no premium plan.<br>
    E2: Duplicate App: Attempting to apply twice to the same project.<br>
    E3: Blacklisted: Client has explicitly blocked the provider from applying.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-121: Cover letters must be at least 150 characters long to discourage spam.<br>
    BR-122: Proposed bids cannot exceed the client's stated maximum budget by more than 50%.<br>
    BR-123: Proposals are hidden from other competing freelancers to maintain confidentiality.
  </td></tr>
</table>

