    AF3: Report violation: Convert a review into a formal report if severe issues occurred.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Rating Unavailable: Contract was terminated early without any work done.<br>
    E2: Duplicate Submit: User tries to rate the same broker twice for one project.<br>
    E3: System Glitch: Rating fails to save due to database lock.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>Medium</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-136: Ratings must satisfy a minimum word count of 30 for high-budget projects.<br>
    BR-137: Reviewers cannot change their star rating once submitted.<br>
    BR-138: Clients/Brokers cannot delete reviews autonomously (requires admin intervention).
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-49 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-49 — Manage User Accounts</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Admin</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Support Team</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Administer system users including verification, suspension, and role changes.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Admin logs into the Control Panel and navigates to 'User Management'.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: User has 'SuperAdmin' or 'Moderator' role.<br>
    PRE2: Multi-factor authentication (MFA) is active for the admin session.<br>
    PRE3: Admin is on a secure, whitelisted IP.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: User status (Active/Suspended/Verified) is updated in the database.<br>
    POST2: Target user receives a system notification about the account change.<br>
    POST3: Admin action is recorded in the immutable system audit log.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Search for a user by Email or ID.<br>
    2. Review user activity and flagged reports.<br>
    3. Update user status or KYC verification state.<br>
    4. Save changes with a reason note.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Ban by IP: Block all accounts associated with a specific malicious IP range.<br>
    AF2: Reset MFA: Manually help a user who lost their 2FA device.<br>
    AF3: Impersonat User: Log in as user (Read-only) to troubleshoot a bug.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Higher-Rank Block: Moderator cannot suspend a SuperAdmin account.<br>
    E2: Missing Reason: System prevents saving changes without a mandatory 'Action Reason'.<br>
    E3: Simultaneous Edit: Two admins trying to modify the same user record.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-139: All 'Account Suspension' actions must be reversible for 30 days.<br>
    BR-140: Admins cannot view user passwords; they can only trigger resets.<br>
    BR-141: Every admin session is recorded via screen-logs for security compliance.
  </td></tr>
</table>

