  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-51 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-51 — Ban Account</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Admin</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Target User</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Permanently or temporarily disable a user's access to the platform due to severe policy violations.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Admin clicks "Ban Account" on a user detail page.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: Target account exists and is not already permanently banned.<br>
    PRE2: Admin has 'Manage Accounts' permission.<br>
    PRE3: A justification/incident report is linked to the action.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Account status is updated to 'BANNED' or 'SUSPENDED' in the database.<br>
    POST2: All active sessions for the user are immediately terminated.<br>
    POST3: System sends a final notice email to the user explaining the ban.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Select ban duration (Temporary/Permanent).<br>
    2. Input specific violation category (Fraud, Harassment, etc.).<br>
    3. Revoke any pending payouts (if applicable).<br>
    4. Confirm ban action.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Shadow Ban: Restrict user visibility without notifying them (used for botting checks).<br>
    AF2: IP Ban: Block the user's primary IP address from accessing the site.<br>
    AF3: Ban with Appeal: Allow the user to submit one appeal within 14 days.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Forbidden Action: Trying to ban a fellow Admin or higher-ranked official.<br>
    E2: Active Escrow: Ban blocked until active funds of the user are safely locked or refunded.<br>
    E3: Database Error: Status update fails, user remains active temporarily.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-145: Permanent bans require a second admin approval for high-tier accounts.<br>
    BR-146: All banned user data must be retained for legal compliance for 5 years.<br>
    BR-147: Banned users are automatically blacklisted from re-registering with the same bank/phone.
  </td></tr>
</table>

