    E1: Session Timeout: Auth expires mid-search.<br>
    E2: Conflict of Interest: Staff member is barred from viewing a dispute where they know a participant.<br>
    E3: Search Limit: Query returns too many results; required to narrow filters.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-163: Disputes are automatically prioritized based on project budget and participant trust scores.<br>
    BR-164: Disputes involving staff family/friends must be 'Hard Locked' from that staff member.<br>
    BR-165: List must highlight cases that are within 12 hours of their response deadline.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-58 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-58 — View Dispute Specific Information</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Admin, Staff</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Plaintiff, Defendant</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Deep-dive into a single dispute case to review evidence, chat history, and previous project specs.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Actor clicks on a Dispute Case ID in the list.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: Case ID is valid and exists.<br>
    PRE2: Admin/Staff session is active.<br>
    PRE3: Case is not 'Private/SuperAdmin Only'.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Unified timeline of all dispute activities is displayed.<br>
    POST2: All uploaded evidence (PDFs, Images, Code) is available for preview.<br>
    POST3: Full project chat history is decrypted for the mediator.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Review the Plaintiff's claim and requested refund amount.<br>
    2. Read the Defendant's counter-argument.<br>
    3. Inspect technical deliverables linked to the milestone.<br>
    4. Compare claims against the original project Specs (UC-30).
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Download Evidence Bundle: Save all case files as a single zip for offline review.<br>
    AF2: View Participant Stats: Check how many disputes each side has won/lost in the past.<br>
    AF3: Activity Feed: See who else (other staff) has viewed this case.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Missing Evidence: Link to file is broken in storage; shows error icon.<br>
    E2: Access Denied: Trying to view a 'Higher-tier' dispute (e.g., Enterprise) without permission.<br>
    E3: Data Mismatch: Dispute balance doesn't match escrow held.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-166: All dispute evidence must be virus-scanned before admin preview.<br>
    BR-167: Viewing a dispute record is tracked via an 'Internal Access Log' including IP.<br>
    BR-168: Participants cannot see that an Admin is currently viewing their case details.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-59 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-59 — Solve Dispute</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Admin, Staff</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Client, Provider</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Issue a final verdict on a dispute case, distributing escrow funds according to the decision.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Actor clicks "Finalize Verdict" in the dispute dashboard.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: All evidence has been reviewed.<br>
    PRE2: Both participants have had their 72-hour window to respond.<br>
    PRE3: Actor has 'Verdict Execution' permission.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Decision is permanently recorded in the case log.<br>
    POST2: Escrow funds are automatically released/refunded based on the split %.<br>
    POST3: Trust scores of involved users are updated based on the outcome.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Input the refund/payment percentages (e.g., 50/50, 100/0).<br>
    2. Write the formal Decision Rationale (visible to both sides).<br>
    3. Select if any platform fees should be waived.<br>
    4. Execute verdict.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Propose Settlement: Suggest a deal to the users and wait for their approval.<br>
    AF2: Escalate to Senior: Send complex cases to high-level managers for the final word.<br>
    AF3: Dismiss Case: Close the dispute with no payout/refund if evidence is insufficient.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Payout Failure: Error transferring funds from escrow to user wallets.<br>
    E2: Edit Locked: Verdict cannot be changed once the 'Execute' button is pressed.<br>
    E3: User Deleted: Participant closed their account mid-dispute; admin override required.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-169: Verdicts must always include a mandatory justification of at least 100 words.<br>
    BR-170: Once a verdict is executed, funds are transferred within 60 minutes.<br>
    BR-171: Decisions on cases >$5,000 require dual-admin confirmation.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-60 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-60 — Manage Freelancer/Broker Registration</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Admin</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Applicant</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Verify and approve/reject applications for specialized provider roles (Broker, Freelancer).</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Admin opens the "Provider Applications" queue.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: New applications have been submitted.<br>
    PRE2: Admin session is active.<br>
    PRE3: KYC data has been extracted from documents.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Account role is confirmed or restricted.<br>
    POST2: Verification badge is applied to the user's profile.<br>
    POST3: Welcome/Rejection email is triggered.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Review applicant's CV and portfolio.<br>
    2. Compare KYC ID image against profile photo.<br>
    3. Check for previous bans linked to the same identity.<br>
    4. Set application status to 'Approved', 'Rejected', or 'Request More Info'.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Auto-verify: System approves users who match high-trust records from LinkedIn APIs.<br>
    AF2: Probationary Approval: Approve with a low job limit for the first 30 days.<br>
    AF3: Blacklist Applicant: Permanently block the identity if fraud is detected.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Unreadable Documents: Uploaded KYC files are too blurry; request new ones.<br>
    E2: Duplicate ID: The same ID card is used across multiple accounts.<br>
    E3: System Timeout: External verification API is down.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-172: Provider applications must be processed within 5 business days.<br>
    BR-173: Rejections for 'Fraud' must not include specific details about detection methods.<br>
    BR-174: Brokers must pass a secondary background check or interview for Enterprise projects.
  </td></tr>
</table>

