<!-- UC-62 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-62 — Send Notification Email</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Admin</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, SMTP Server, User Base</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Manually trigger system-wide or targeted email notifications for announcements or warnings.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Admin clicks "Broadcast Email" in the Communications tool.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: Admin has 'Communications Manager' role.<br>
    PRE2: Email templates are pre-defined or editable.<br>
    PRE3: Target user list is non-empty.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Emails are queued in the background worker.<br>
    POST2: Delivery and Open rates tracking is initialized.<br>
    POST3: A copy of the broadcast is saved in the 'Announcement Archive'.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Select Target Group (All Users, Only Brokers, etc.).<br>
    2. Choose Email Template (Update, Warning, New Feature).<br>
    3. Preview the email with dynamic tags variables.<br>
    4. Click 'Blast Now'.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Scheduled Send: Set the email to be sent at a specific future UTC time.<br>
    AF2: A/B Testing: Send two versions to small segments to compare effectiveness.<br>
    AF3: Personal Warning: Send an email only to a single user about a specific issue.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Bounce Limit: Too many failed deliveries cause the SMTP to pause automatically.<br>
    E2: Invalid Template: Syntax errors in the HTML code prevent rendering.<br>
    E3: Unsubscribe Conflict: Trying to send marketing to users who opted out.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>Medium</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-178: All manual emails must include a mandatory 'Unsubscribe' or 'Manage Preferences' link.<br>
    BR-179: Broadcasts to over 10,000 users must be approved by the CTO.<br>
    BR-180: System-critical notifications (bans/disputes) bypass the user's opt-out settings.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-63 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-63 — View List Feedback</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Admin, Staff</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Users</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>Monitor all project completion reviews and platform feedback left by users.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>Actor navigates to the "Review Moderation" dashboard.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: Actor has 'Moderator' or 'Admin' role.<br>
    PRE2: Feedback data is available in the database.<br>
    PRE3: Session is active.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: List of latest reviews across all projects is shown.<br>
    POST2: Average platform trust score is updated in the summary.<br>
    POST3: Negative reviews are flagged for staff investigation.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Browse reviews by project ID.<br>
    2. Identify reviews containing 'Trigger Keywords' (Scam, Rude, Bad Code).<br>
    3. Check for 'Retaliatory' rating patterns between two users.<br>
    4. Approve reviews for public display.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Hide Review: Temporarily unpublish a review that is under investigation.<br>
    AF2: Direct Response: Post an official platform response to a public review.<br>
    AF3: Sentiment Analytics: View a word cloud of common feedback themes.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Data Leak: Private feedback meant for admins showing up in the public list.<br>
    E2: Massive Spam: Review queue flooded by bot accounts.<br>
    E3: Attachment Error: Unable to view the technical 'Deliverable' linked to the review.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>Medium</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-181: Reviews cannot be edited by staff; only hidden or deleted via 'Hard Policy'.<br>
    BR-182: Reviews for projects involving 'Disputes' are held for 14 days before publishing.<br>
    BR-183: Community trust scores are updated every 24 hours based on new feedback.
  </td></tr>
</table>

<!-- UC-64 -->
<table>
  <tr><th class="header-cell">ID and Name:</th><td class="header-cell"><b>UC-64 — Check KYC Status</b></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Created By:</th><td>AnNPCE</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Date Created:</th><td>15/01/2026</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Primary Actor:</th><td>Client, Broker, Freelancer</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Secondary Actors:</th><td>System, Verification Service</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Description:</th><td>User checks the current state of their identity verification submission.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Trigger:</th><td>User clicks "Account Verification" in their profile settings.</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Preconditions:</th><td>
    PRE1: User is logged in.<br>
    PRE2: Verification documents were previously submitted.<br>
    PRE3: Account is not already 'Permanently Banned'.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Postconditions:</th><td>
    POST1: Current status (In Review, Verified, Rejected, Missing Info) is shown.<br>
    POST2: Reason for rejection is provided (if status is 'Rejected').<br>
    POST3: Instructions for next steps are displayed clearly.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Normal Flow:</th><td>
    1. Open Verification Dashboard.<br>
    2. Read current status badge.<br>
    3. View timestamp of last update.<br>
    4. See which specific documents were accepted/denied.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Alternative Flows:</th><td>
    AF1: Re-submit Documents: Upload new photos if the old ones were rejected.<br>
    AF2: Appeal Rejection: Ask for manual review if the automated AI system failed.<br>
    AF3: View Benefits: Read what new platform features unlock at this status.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Exceptions:</th><td>
    E1: Status Loading: System displays "Please wait, fetching verification data...".<br>
    E2: Missing Record: User thinks they submitted but system has no entry.<br>
    E3: Access Revoked: Verification page disabled because the user tried to upload fraudulent IDs too many times.
  </td></tr>
  <tr><th>Priority:</th><td>High</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Business Rules:</th><td>
    BR-184: Users are limited to 3 KYC submission attempts per 30 days.<br>
    BR-185: Being 'Verified' is mandatory for withdrawing funds >$500.<br>
    BR-186: KYC status is automatically downgraded if ID document expires.
  </td></tr>
</table>

